Female followers who have been pregnant: While you were pregnant, did you have an easier or harder time reading and focusing on longer form texts: big books, old novels, doorstoppers, Balzac or Goethe type stuff, etc.? Important question for science.

The mechanism I have in mind is very simple: There are studies showing progesterone influences time perception. If bad time perception is why some people struggle to read anything longer than 2 pages, then third trimester might set them in a state where reading a novel is easier.

If you know time perception is biological and related to brain glucose consumption rate, it seems very likely that the sensation of time "slipping away from you" that comes with low metabolism or estrogens also makes it harder to read longer texts. Progesterone = reading hormone.
